It is made by cooking together milk, sugar, and a special ingredient called doda, which is a type of edible gum resin extracted from the bark of the axlewood tree. info.name: Besan Chakki
info.description: Besan Chakki sweet is a traditional and popular Indian sweet dish combining the finest ingredients such as gram flour, ghee, sugar & Cardamom. Prepared in a traditional method of churning with a stone mill or chakki, this sweet delicacy has a delectable aroma that makes it hard to resist. Besan Chakki tantalizes everyone's taste buds and makes for an unforgettable culinary experience.

info.name: Double Burfi
info.description: Double burfi is a type of sweet dessert that originated in India. It is made by mixing together two types of burfi, which are traditional Indian sweets made with milk solids (khoya), sugar, and flavorings.

info.name: Dry Fruit Halwa
info.description:
Dry fruit halwa is a rich and delicious dessert that is popular in India and other parts of South Asia. It is made by cooking together a variety of dried fruits, nuts, sugar, and ghee (clarified butter) until it forms a thick, fudgy consistency.
The specific ingredients used in dry fruit halwa can vary, but some common ones include raisins, apricots, figs, cashews, almonds, and pistachios.

info.name: Milk Mysore Pak

info.name: Coconut Kalakand
info.description: Coconut kalakand is a delicious Indian dessert made from coconut, milk, sugar, and paneer (cottage cheese). It is a variation of the traditional kalakand, which is a milk-based sweet that originated in the Indian state of Uttar Pradesh.

info.name: Bombay Halwa
info.description: Bombay halwa, also known as Karachi halwa, is a popular Indian sweet that originated in the city of Karachi (now in Pakistan) but is now widely available in Mumbai and other parts of India. It is a gelatinous sweet made from cornflour, sugar, ghee (clarified butter), and various flavorings such as saffron, cardamom, and rose water.

info.name: Malai Burfi
info.description: Malai burfi is a traditional Indian sweet made from milk, sugar, and flavorings such as cardamom, saffron, or rosewater. The word "malai" means cream, which is the main ingredient used to make this sweet.

info.name: Badusha
info.description: White Flour, Ghee And Sugar To Create A Sweet With Shahiness In Its Surname.

info.name: Gulab Burfi
info.description: Gulab Burfi is a popular Indian sweet that is a combination of Gulab Jamun and Burfi. It is a delicious and unique sweet that is perfect for special occasions or festivals.

info.name: Gound Laddu
info.description: "Ground Laddu" is a term that is not familiar to me. However, "Laddu" is a popular Indian sweet that is made with flour, sugar, and ghee (clarified butter). It is a ball-shaped sweet that is often served at festivals and special occasions.

info.name: Pilani Peda
info.description: Pilani Peda is a famous traditional sweet from the town of Pilani in Rajasthan, India. It is a type of peda, which is a milk-based sweet. Pilani Peda is made using khoa (solidified milk), sugar, and traditional Indian spices such as cardamom and saffron.

info.name: Son Patti
info.description: Soan Patti has a unique texture that is both flaky and chewy, with a sweet, nutty flavor. It is a must-try for anyone with a sweet tooth, and is sure to be a hit at any festive occasion.

info.name: Ajmer Burfi
info.description: A Balanced Ensemble Of The Minimal Basic Of Milk, Sugar And Cardamom Yet When Synchronised With Ghee And Almond Nuts Is Born The Square-Shaped Marvel Right From The Heave Ajmer.

info.name: Sweet Samosa
info.description: Sweet samosas are made by filling the pastry with a sweet filling made from ingredients like khoya (milk solids), coconut, nuts, and sugar. The filling is flavored with cardamom or other spices to give it a fragrant, aromatic flavor.

info.name: Round Peda
info.description: Round Peda is a popular Indian sweet that originated in the state of Uttar Pradesh. It is a soft, fudge-like sweet made from khoya (milk solids), sugar, and various flavorings like cardamom, saffron, and pistachios. The mixture is kneaded and shaped into small, round balls that are then flattened slightly to give them their characteristic shape.

info.name: Shagun Laddu
info.description: Shagun Laddu is a popular sweet dish from the Indian state of Punjab. It is a type of laddu (round-shaped sweet) made from flour, ghee (clarified butter), sugar, and various nuts and dried fruits.

info.name: Ribbon Pakodi - 150Gms
info.description: Ribbon Pakodi, also known as Ribbon Murukku, is a popular savory snack in India. It is similar to regular Murukku, but with a ribbon-like shape and a slightly different texture.

info.name: Doddu Sev - 200Gms
info.description: Doddu Sev is a popular Indian snack made from chickpea flour (besan). It is a crispy and savory snack that is enjoyed on its own or as a topping for chaat and other Indian snacks.

info.name: Dal Mot - 200Gms
info.description: This Ever So Popular Indian Munch Is A Magical Mixed Bag Of Masoor Dal, Premium Cashew, Barik Sev Infused With Basic Indian Spices.

info.name: Crunch Mix - 200Gms
info.description: Crunch Mixture is a popular snack in India made with a combination of different ingredients such as puffed rice, roasted chickpeas, peanuts, sev (thin fried noodles made from gram flour), and spices. It is a crunchy and savory snack that is enjoyed by people of all ages.

info.name: Chena Meva - 200Gms
info.description: Carefully selected and hygienically packed, the Chena Meva is filled with the goodness of fine lentils and refined oil.

info.name: Chekkinalu - 200Gms
info.description: Chekkinalu Is a special type of snack prepared in the northern region of Telangana, India. It consists of concentric circles made of rice flour dough, fried in oil.

info.name: Chekkalu - 200Gms
info.description: A Grand Ensemble Of Rice, Chana Dal Onions And Sabudana Overlaid With Sparks Of Jeera Ginger And Green Chili. A Perfect Teatime Cracker.

info.name: Chat Phat Sticks - 200Gms
info.description: Chat Phat Sticks is a popular Indian snack that is made with potato sticks (aloo sev) and spices. It is a spicy, tangy and crispy snack that can be enjoyed on its own or as a topping for chaat and other Indian snacks.

info.name: Boondi - 200Gms

info.name: Mota Sev - 200Gms
info.description: Mota Sevu has a crunchy texture and a savory taste, making it a great snack to enjoy with tea or as an accompaniment to other dishes. It can be seasoned with different spices like red chili powder, chaat masala, and black pepper to add more flavor. Mota Sevu can be stored in an airtight container for several days and makes for a great on-the-go snack.

info.name: Moong Dal - 200Gms
info.description: Moong dal is a type of split lentil that is commonly used in Indian cuisine. It is made from hulled and split mung beans, which are small, green legumes. Moong dal is a rich source of protein, dietary fiber, and essential nutrients like iron, magnesium, and potassium.

info.name: Milk Matri - 200Gms
info.description: "Milk Mathri" is a type of savory snack that is popular in India. It is made using a combination of flour, ghee or oil, and milk, which is mixed together to form a dough. The dough is then rolled out and cut into small circles or squares, which are then deep-fried until they become crispy and golden brown. Milk Mathri is usually seasoned with spices such as cumin, black pepper, and ajwain, which gives it a distinct flavor and aroma.

info.name: Meva Chuduva - 200Gms
info.description: Mewa Chuduwa is a type of snack or savory mixture popular in Sri Lanka and South India. It is typically made by mixing various nuts, fried lentils (dal), spices, and sometimes dried fruits together. The mixture is then seasoned with spices such as chili powder, turmeric, and salt, and often includes some form of souring agent like tamarind or lime juice. Mewa Chuduwa is a delicious and crunchy snack that can be enjoyed on its own or as a topping for rice dishes.

info.name: Masala Palli - 200Gms
info.description: Masala Palli, also known as Masala Peanuts or Spicy Peanuts, is a popular Indian snack made from roasted peanuts that are seasoned with a blend of spices. It is a delicious and crunchy snack that is perfect to enjoy with tea or drinks during parties, gatherings, and festivals.

info.name: Masala Kaju - 200Gms
info.description: Masala Kaju is a spicy and flavorful Indian snack made from cashew nuts that are seasoned with a blend of spices. It is a popular snack to enjoy with tea or drinks during parties, gatherings, and festivals.

info.name: Masala Chekkalu - 200Gms
info.description: Masala Chekkalu is a popular South Indian snack made from rice flour, chana dal (split chickpeas), and spices. It is also known as rice crackers or rice murukku. The snack has a crispy and crunchy texture, and it's perfect to have with tea or coffee.

info.name: Spiced Corn Flakes - 200Gms
info.description: Makkai Chudwa is a popular snack from the northern parts of India, especially in the state of Punjab. It is a savory snack made from corn kernels that are roasted or fried until crisp and then mixed with spices.

info.name: Khara Khaja - 200Gms
info.description: Khara Khaja is a popular sweet snack from the Indian state of Odisha. It is a deep-fried pastry made from refined flour, ghee, and sugar syrup. The pastry is rolled out thinly and then cut into diamond or square shapes, which are then deep-fried until golden brown and crispy.

info.name: Khara Gavvalu - 200Gms
info.description: Khara gavvalu is a traditional South Indian snack that is popularly made during festivals and special occasions. It is also known as chegodilu in some regions. Khara gavvalu are crunchy, deep-fried, and savory treats that have a unique shape similar to a shell or a twisted knot.

info.name: Karela Chips - 150Gms
info.description: Karela chips are a popular Indian snack made from bitter gourd (also known as karela). To make karela chips, the bitter gourd is sliced thinly and then deep-fried until crisp. The chips are usually seasoned with salt, chili powder, and other spices to add flavor.

info.name: Kaju Pakodi - 200Gms
info.description: Kaju pakoda is a popular Indian snack made from cashew nuts that are coated in a spicy gram flour (besan) batter and deep-fried until crispy. It is a crispy and crunchy snack that can be enjoyed with a cup of tea or coffee.

info.name: Ghati Mixture - 200Gms
info.description: Ghati Mixture is a popular snack in the Indian state of Maharashtra. It is a spicy and tangy mixture of different ingredients like puffed rice, roasted peanuts, sev (thin fried noodles made from gram flour), dried coconut, and spices.

info.name: Salted Kaju - 200Gms

info.name: Sabudana Chudva - 200Gms
info.description: Sabudana Chudwa, also known as Sabudana Mixture, is a popular snack in India that is made from sabudana, which are also called tapioca pearls. Sabudana is gluten-free and is a good source of carbohydrates, making it a popular food during fasting or religious occasions.

info.name: Roasted Salted Foxnuts - 80Gms
info.description: Roasted Salted Foxnuts, also known as Roasted Salted Makhana, is a popular snack in India that is made from foxnuts, which are also called lotus seeds. Foxnuts are low in calories and fat and are a good source of protein, fiber, and minerals like magnesium and potassium.

info.name: Roasted Kaju - 200Gms
info.description: Roasted Kaju, also known as Roasted Cashews, is a popular snack in India that is enjoyed for its crunchy texture and delicious flavor. Cashews are a good source of healthy fats, protein, and minerals like magnesium and zinc.

info.name: Roasted Badam - 200Gms
info.description: Roasted Badam, also known as Roasted Almonds, is a healthy and delicious snack that is enjoyed all over the world. Almonds are a rich source of nutrients, including healthy fats, protein, fiber, and vitamins and minerals like vitamin E, magnesium, and calcium.

info.name: Palak Sev - 200Gms
info.description: Palak Sev is a popular Indian snack made from spinach and chickpea flour. It is a healthy and nutritious snack that is also gluten-free and vegan.

info.name: Namak Para - 200Gms
info.description: Namak Para is a popular savory snack in India that is also known as Nimki or Namak Pare. It is made from a simple dough made from all-purpose flour, salt, and water, which is then rolled out and cut into diamond or square shapes. The dough is then deep-fried until golden brown and crispy.

info.name: Murukulu - 200Gms
info.description: Murukulu, also known as Murukku, is a popular savory snack in South India. It is made using a combination of rice flour, urad dal flour, and spices, which are mixed together to form a dough. The dough is then extruded through a mold or a press with different designs and shapes, such as spiral or flower-shaped, and deep-fried until crispy and golden brown.

info.name: Murmura Chudva - 200Gms
info.description: Murmura Chudwa, also known as Puffed Rice Chivda or Puffed Rice Mixture, is a popular snack in India and other South Asian countries. info.name: Banana Chips - 200Gms

info.name: Angur Gulab Jamun
info.description: Angoor Gulab Jamun is a dessert that originates from the Indian subcontinent. It is essentially small, round, and syrupy dumplings made from milk solids (khoya) and flour, which are deep-fried until golden brown and then soaked in rose-flavored sugar syrup.

info.name: Rabdi
info.description: Rabdi, also known as rabri, is a popular Indian dessert that is made by boiling and reducing milk to a thick, creamy consistency. The milk is simmered on low heat for a long time until it thickens and turns into a custard-like consistency. Rabdi is often flavored with cardamom, saffron, and chopped nuts such as pistachios and almonds.

info.name: Jangri
info.description: Jangri, also known as Jhangri, is a popular South Indian sweet dish made with fermented urad dal batter that is fried and soaked in sugar syrup. It is similar to the North Indian sweet dish Jalebi.

info.name: Ras Gulla[Per Piece]
info.description: Rasgulla is a popular Indian sweet made from chenna (cottage cheese) and cooked in a sugar syrup. To make rasgulla, chenna is prepared by curdling milk with lemon juice or vinegar. The curdled milk is then drained and kneaded to form a smooth dough-like consistency.

info.name: Corn Samosa[Per Piece]
info.description: Corn samosa is a popular Indian snack that is made by stuffing a pastry with a spicy corn filling. To make corn samosas, a dough made of all-purpose flour, salt, and oil is kneaded and then rolled into thin sheets. The sheets are then cut into triangles and filled with a mixture of boiled corn kernels, onions, green chilies, and spices such as cumin, coriander, turmeric, and garam masala.

info.name: Matar Kachori[Per Piece]
info.description: Matar kachori is a popular Indian snack that is made by stuffing a pastry with a spicy green peas filling. To make matar kachori, a dough made of all-purpose flour, salt, and oil is kneaded and then rolled into thin sheets. The sheets are then cut into circles and filled with a mixture of green peas, onions, and spices such as cumin, coriander, fennel seeds, ginger, and garam masala.

info.name: Alu Samosa[Per Piece]
info.description: Aloo samosa is a popular Indian snack that is made by stuffing a pastry with a savory filling made of spiced potatoes. To make aloo samosa, a dough made of all-purpose flour, salt, and oil is kneaded and then rolled into thin sheets. The sheets are then cut into triangles and filled with a mixture of boiled and mashed potatoes, peas, onions, and spices such as cumin, coriander, turmeric, and garam masala.

info.name: Honey Jilebi
info.description: Honey jalebi is a variation of the traditional jalebi, where honey is used as a sweetener instead of sugar syrup.

info.name: Angoor Rasmalai
info.description: Angoor Rasmalai is a popular Indian dessert that is made from soft and spongy cottage cheese balls (also called rasgullas) that are soaked in a creamy and sweetened milk sauce flavored with saffron, cardamom, and rose water.

info.name: Onion Kachori[Per Piece]
info.description: Onion kachori is a popular Indian snack that is made by stuffing a pastry with a spicy onion filling. To make onion kachori, a dough made of all-purpose flour, salt, and oil is kneaded and then rolled into thin sheets. The sheets are then cut into circles and filled with a mixture of onions, gram flour, and spices such as cumin, coriander, fennel seeds, ginger, and chili powder.

info.name: Badam Milk 200Ml[200Ml]
info.description: Badam milk is a popular beverage in India made from almond milk and flavored with spices such as cardamom, saffron, and rose water. It is often served warm or chilled and can be enjoyed as a dessert or a healthy drink.
